Nike Popoola Linkage Assurance Plc says its profit after tax rose by 16 per cent for the half-year unaudited financial statement ended June 30. A statement from the firm said the figure rose from N439.77m in the half-year period of 2018 to N572.76m in the same period in 2019. According to the financial statement made available to the Nigerian Stock Exchange, Linkage posted a gross premium written income of N4.13bn as against N3.65bn the previous year. With efficient risk management, the underwriter during the period returned to profitability in underwriting performance, posting a 176 per cent increase, as the figure moved from negative N367.11m in 2018 to positive N296.06m. Linkage Assurance’ total assets also grew by eight per cent from N23.146bn to N24.869bn as of the end of June 2019. The company said it was optimistic that it would sustain the growth all year around, as its growth initiatives already deployed were beginning to add value to the performance of the company. The Managing Director of Linkage Assurance Plc, Daniel Braie, said the company had diversified its portfolio to achieve income efficiency with quality risk management. He noted that the management was actively watching its cost to ensure that it delivered value to shareholders. “In terms of compliance to regulatory requirements, we are up and doing to ensure we remain above board and maintain our position in the industry,” Braie said. Linkage Assurance was registered by the National Insurance Commission on the October 7, 1993 to transact general insurance business and began operation in January 1994. Copyright PUNCH.                
